"1235–1300","1276–1327":"1276–1327","1315–Female":"1315–Afdød","–Male":"Afdød","1250–1325":"1250–1325","1253–Female":"1253–Afdød","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1325":"1325","1224":"1224","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","Abt 1276":"omkring 1276","1276":"1276","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Norton Disney, North Kesteven, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England","Delamere, Cheshire, England":"Delamere, Cheshire, England"},"nl":{"–1293":"–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300","1276–1327":"1276–1327","1315–Female":"1315–Overleden","–Male":"Overleden","1250–1325":"1250–1325","1253–Female":"1253–Overleden","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1325":"1325","1224":"1224","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","Abt 1276":"circa 1276","1276":"1276","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Norton Disney, North Kesteven, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England","Delamere, Cheshire, England":"Delamere, Cheshire, England"},"en":{"–1293":"–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300","1276–1327":"1276–1327","1315–Female":"1315–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1250–1325":"1250–1325","1253–Female":"1253–Deceased","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1325":"1325","1224":"1224","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","Abt 1276":"about 1276","1276":"1276","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Norton Disney, North Kesteven, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England","Delamere, Cheshire, England":"Delamere, Cheshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"d'Isney","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name with fused French preposition <i>d(e)</i>, for someone from Isigny in Calvados, France, named from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Isinius</i> (a Latinized form of Gaulish <i>Isina</i>) + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Violet  ,   Vivien  , or   Vivian ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vivien","meanings":["Earlier generally taken as a variant of the boy's name   Vivian  , but now also rarely used for boys. This spelling was quite common in Old French. Its use as a girl's name in the English-speaking world was influenced by  Tennyson's  Merlin and Vivien (  1859 ). This name, from Arthurian legend, may represent an altered form of a Celtic name (perhaps akin to the Irish Gaelic name <i>Béibhinn</i> ‘white lady’, pronounced ‘bee-<b>veen</b>’). The actress  Vivien Leigh  (  1913–67 ) was christened <i>Vivian</i>."]},{"name":"Violet","meanings":["From the name of the flower (Old French <i>violette</i>, Late Latin <i>violetta</i>, a diminutive of <i>viola</i>). This was one of the earliest flower names to become popular in Britain, being used as early as  1700  and becoming well established in the 19th century, although it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":40,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":49,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":84,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":115,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William II d'Isney was born in Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England as the son of Sir William d'Isney I and Berthsheba Ormesby. He married Jane de Dive in 1276, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1293, in his hometown, and was buried in Delamere, Cheshire, England."},"et":{"–1293":"–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300","1276–1327":"1276–1327","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1250–1325":"1250–1325","1253–Female":"1253–Surnud","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1325":"1325","1224":"1224","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","Abt 1276":"umbes 1276","1276":"1276","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norton Disney, North Kesteven, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England","Delamere, Cheshire, England":"Delamere, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"–1293":"–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300","1276–1327":"1276–1327","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1250–1325":"1250–1325","1253–Female":"1253–Kuollut","1253":"1253","1250":"1250","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1325":"1325","1224":"1224","1235":"1235","1300":"1300","Abt 1276":"noin 1276","1276":"1276","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norton Disney, North Kesteven, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England":"Norton Disney, Lincolnshire, England","Delamere, Cheshire, England":"Delamere, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"–1293":"–1293","1235–1300":"1235–1300",